Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with winged caduceus symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 31, 13. Name Philon. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0012.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0751)
